parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can result in injury or death.
symptoms: The ABS light stays on
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle continues to move without braking
the brakes lock up
the vehicle skids or loses control
the brakes make a hissing sound

the brake pedal sticks to the floor
